commit.message:
feat(dokploy): add DeployBypassToken for WAF/bot-protection bypass

Adds an optional X-Deploy-Token header to all Dokploy API requests.
Configure your reverse proxy or WAF in front of the Dokploy VPS to
skip bot protection / rate limiting when this header is present.

Works with: Cloudflare WAF Custom Rule, Nginx, Traefik, Caddy, HAProxy.

Usage in AppHost:
  builder.PublishToDokploy("my-app", s => {
      s.DokployUrl = "https://paas.example.com";
      s.DeployBypassToken = config["Dokploy:BypassToken"]; // from CI secret
  });

